<body>
  <main>
    <div class="card">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated: 2026-03-02</p>

      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        NoteAI provides transcription and AI-assisted summarization features. This policy explains what data we
        collect/process, how we use it, and when it is shared with service providers.
      </p>

      <h2>Data We Collect and Process</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>User content:</strong> audio recordings you upload/record, transcripts, and text you submit for summaries or chat.</li>
        <li><strong>Account and app data:</strong> basic account identifiers (if you create an account) and subscription status.</li>
        <li><strong>Diagnostics:</strong> crash logs and performance data (if enabled on your device / via analytics you use).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Third-Party Processing (AI Services)</h2>
      <p>
        When you use transcription or AI summary features, NoteAI may transmit your content to third-party service providers
        to process it and return results to the app. This can include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Audio recordings (for speech-to-text transcription)</li>
        <li>Transcript text and/or user-provided text (for summary generation)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Providers may include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>AssemblyAI</strong> – speech-to-text processing</li>
        <li><strong>OpenAI</strong> – text generation/summarization</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We send this data only to provide requested features and only after you provide consent in the app. If you do not
        consent, AI processing will not occur.
      </p>

      <h2>How We Use Data</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide transcription, summaries, and related app functionality.</li>
        <li>Maintain security, prevent abuse, and improve reliability.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain your content only as long as needed to provide the service and for legitimate business purposes such as
        troubleshooting, unless a longer retention period is required by law.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Choices</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You can decline AI consent in the app. Without consent, AI processing features are disabled.</li>
        <li>You can request deletion of your data by contacting us (see below).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Email: <a href="mailto:support@yourdomain.com">support@yourdomain.com</a>
        <span class="muted">(replace with your real support email)</span>
      </p>

      <p class="muted" style="margin-top:18px">
        Notes: Update provider names and sections to exactly match your production configuration and App Store privacy answers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</body>
